{
    "name":  "03 - Notification Router (Shared Subworkflow)",
    "nodes":  [
                  {
                      "parameters":  {
                                         "content":  "## ðŸ“£ Notification Router\n\n**Purpose:** Routes a notification to one or more channels (Slack, email, Telegram) based on configuration.\n\n**Setup:**\n1. Create credentials for each channel you want to use:\n   - Slack: credential named `Slack API`\n   - Email: credential named `SMTP Email`\n   - Telegram: credential named `Telegram API`\n2. Set environment variables:\n   - `SLACK_CHANNEL_ALERTS` e.g. `#product-alerts`\n   - `NOTIFICATION_EMAIL_TO` e.g. `team@example.com`\n   - `TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID` e.g. `123456789`\n\n**Input:**\n```json\n{\n  \"channel\": \"slack | email | telegram | all\",\n  \"title\": \"string\",\n  \"body\": \"string (markdown OK)\",\n  \"urgency\": \"low | medium | high\",\n  \"metadata\": {}\n}\n```",
                                         "height":  380,
                                         "width":  480,
                                         "color":  5
                                     },
                      "id":  "sticky-router-setup",
                      "name":  "Setup Instructions",
                      "type":  "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
                      "typeVersion":  1,
                      "position":  [
                                       0,
                                       -220
                                   ]
                  },
                  {
                      "parameters":  {

                                     },
                      "id":  "trigger-router",
                      "name":  "When Called by Another Workflow",
                      "type":  "n8n-nodes-base.executeWorkflowTrigger",
                      "typeVersion":  1,
                      "position":  [
                                       240,
                                       100
                                   ]
                  },
                  {
                      "parameters":  {
                                         "jsCode":  "const input = $input.first().json;\n\nconst channel = (input.channel || \u0027email\u0027).toLowerCase();\nconst urgency = (input.urgency || \u0027low\u0027).toLowerCase();\n\n// Determine which channels to send to\nconst sendToSlack = channel === \u0027slack\u0027 || channel === \u0027all\u0027;\nconst sendToEmail = channel === \u0027email\u0027 || channel === \u0027all\u0027;\nconst sendToTelegram = channel === \u0027telegram\u0027 || channel === \u0027all\u0027;\n\n// Urgency emoji\nconst urgencyEmoji = { high: \u0027ðŸš¨\u0027, medium: \u0027âš ï¸\u0027, low: \u0027â„¹ï¸\u0027 }[urgency] || \u0027â„¹ï¸\u0027;\n\nreturn [{\n  json: {\n    ...input,\n    sendToSlack,\n    sendToEmail,\n    sendToTelegram,\n    urgencyEmoji,\n    slackChannel: process.env.SLACK_CHANNEL_ALERTS || \u0027#product-alerts\u0027,\n    emailTo: process.env.NOTIFICATION_EMAIL_TO || \u0027team@example.com\u0027,\n    telegramChatId: process.env.TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID || \u0027YOUR_TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID\u0027,\n    formattedTitle: `${urgencyEmoji} ${input.title}`,\n  }\n}];"
                                     },
                      "id":  "prepare-notification",
                      "name":  "Prepare Notification",
                      "type":  "n8n-nodes-base.code",
                      "typeVersion":  2,
                      "position":  [
                                       460,
                                       100
                                   ]
                  },
                  {
                      "parameters":  {
                                         "conditions":  {
                                                            "options":  {
                                                                            "caseSensitive":  false,
                                                                            "leftValue":  "",
                                                                            "typeValidation":  "strict"
                                                                        },
                                                            "conditions":  [
                                                                               {
                                                                                   "id":  "send-slack-condition",
                                                                                   "leftValue":  "={{ $json.sendToSlack }}",
                                                                                   "rightValue":  true,
                                                                                   "operator":  {
                                                                                                    "type":  "boolean",
                                                                                                    "operation":  "equal"
                                                                                                }
                                                                               }
                                                                           ],
                                                            "combinator":  "and"
                                                        }
                                     },
                      "id":  "check-slack",
                      "name":  "Send to Slack?",
